President Obama expresses his sadness and pays tribute to John Wooden, a legendary basketball coach known for his humility and dedication to the betterment of others. Obama remembers Wooden's numerous NCAA championships and his unmatched winning streak at UCLA, but he also admires how Wooden achieved success with modesty and wholeheartedly dedicated his life to teaching and preparing his players. Wooden's impact extended beyond the court as he continued to teach and inspire others. Obama acknowledges that Wooden missed the practice and preparation the most, not the tournaments or games. The President also sends his thoughts and prayers to Wooden's family, including his children, grandchildren, and great-grandchildren, as they mourn his passing.